sys_remote_update_set.description:
Tables : - FTP Transation : to store any transaction between PRIAM and Daisy - FTP Company Code : to store PRIAM company codes
Properties : - td.france.ftp.mid.server - td.france.ftp.priam.ip.address - td.france.ftp.password - td.france.ftp.username - td.france.ftp.mid.server.temp.path - td.france.ftp.priam.ispassive - td.france.ftp.priam.transport.method - td.france.ftp.priam.port - td.france.ftp.priam.host
UI Action : - Send to PRIAM : used to send manually files (FTP Transaction) to PRIAM. The file is stored in the mid server (td.france.ftp.mid.server.temp.path)
Business Rule : - TD - Create CAR IN transactions : create FTP transaction where the To field is "CAR" when ECC Queue response is created and linked to a donwload from PRIAM
MID Server Script Include - MidServerIntegration : all used functions to upload, donwload and delete files in FTP Sever, create files in a server and get and send information to ServiceNow
Script Include : - MidServerIntegrationCalls : functions used to call the MID Server Script Include "MidServerIntegration". The scripts are called by the BR "TD - Create CAR IN transactions" and
sys_remote_update_set.name: Daisy - FTP Server integration V1.0

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_include"><sys_script_include action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>package_private</access><active>true</active><api_name>global.MidServerIntegrationCalls</api_name><client_callable>false</client_callable><description/><name>MidServerIntegrationCalls</name><script><![CDATA[var MidServerIntegrationCalls = Class.create();
MidServerIntegrationCalls.prototype = {
	/**
 	* Description:
 	*             Initialize all needed parameters
 	* Parameters:
 	*             ftp_connec
 	* Returns:
 	*             none
 	*/
	initialize: function() {
		try{
			this.host = gs.getProperty('td.france.ftp.priam.host');
			this.port = gs.getProperty('td.france.ftp.priam.port');
			this.mid = gs.getProperty('td.france.ftp.mid.server');
			this.user = gs.getProperty('td.france.ftp.username');
			this.password = gs.getProperty('td.france.ftp.password');
			this.ispassive = gs.getProperty('td.france.ftp.priam.ispassive');
			this.transport = gs.getProperty('td.france.ftp.priam.transport.method');
			this.targetpath = gs.getProperty('td.france.ftp.mid.server.temp.path');
			
		} catch(e){
			gs.logError("Error in the function MidServerIntegrationCalls().initialize() : "+ e, "Script Include");
		}
	},
	/**
 	* Description:
 	*             Create probe MidServerIntegration.copyFiles from a remote directory
 	* Parameters:
 	*             filepath : directory from which the file are downloaded
 	* Returns:
 	*/
	
	/* List files in the provided remote directory */
	copyFiles: function(filepath, code) {
		
		try {
			var jspr = new JavascriptProbe(this.mid);
			jspr.setName(code);
			jspr.setSource('ftp');
			jspr.setJavascript('var sc = new MidServerIntegration; var res = sc.copyFiles();');
			//jspr.setJavascript('var sc = new TD_FTPTransactionsMID; var res = sc.listFiles();');
			jspr.addParameter('host', this.host);
			jspr.addParameter('port', this.port);
			jspr.addParameter('user', this.user);
			jspr.addParameter('password', this.password);
			jspr.addParameter('filepath',filepath);
			jspr.addParameter('targetpath', this.targetpath);
			return jspr.create();
			
		} catch(e) {
			gs.logError("Error in the function MidServerIntegration().copyFiles()  :"+ e,"Script Include");
		}
	},
	
	buildPRIAMFile: function(ftpTransac){
		var fileName = ftpTransac.u_file_name;
		var midServerTempPath = this.targetpath
		/*+'\\'+ftpTransac.u_to.getDisplayValue()+'\\IN'*/;
		var fileDestinationPath = '/'+ftpTransac.u_from.getDisplayValue()
		+'/OUT/';
		var ftpServer =  this.host;
		var ftpPort = this.port;
		var userName = this.user;
		var password = this.password;
		var passive = this.ispassive;
		var ftp_transport_method =  this.transport;
		var file_format = ftpTransac.u_type;
		
		var request = [];
		if (!fileName){
			gs.addInfoMessage("You didn't specify a file name so the default name will be defaultFileName.csv");
			fileName = "defaultFileName."+ ftpTransac.u_type;
		}
		request.push(fileName);
		
		//Start the process
		gs.log('Building file..');
		var mid = this.mid;
		request.push(mid);
		
		if (!mid){
			gs.log("A MID Server has not been set for the FTP Connection");
		}
		else {
			gs.log("The MID Server being used to build the file is: " + mid);
		}
		
		var output       = "";
		var padding      = "";
		var outputArray = [];
		var startTime, endTime, elapsed;
		var interval  = 1000;
		var count     = 0;
		var fileCount = 0;
		
		startTime = new Date().getTime();
		line = ftpTransac.u_content;
		
		// Add the line to the main output var
		outputArray.push(line);	
		fileCount++;
		output += outputArray.join('');
		
		var props = {
			"mid_server":   mid,
			"payload":      GlideStringUtil.base64Encode(output),
			"part_number":  fileCount,
			"temp_path":    midServerTempPath,
			"file_name":    fileName
		};
		
		this._sendFilePartToMIDServer(props);
		output = "";
		outputArray = [];
		
		// Send finish file
		var finishPayload = "";
		finishPayload += "filename=" + fileName + "\r\n";
		finishPayload += "filecount=" + fileCount + "\r\n";

		this._sendFinishFileToMIDServer({
			"mid_server":  mid,
			"payload":     GlideStringUtil.base64Encode(finishPayload),
			"file_count":  fileCount,
			"temp_path":   midServerTempPath,
			"file_name":   fileName,
			"ftp_server":  ftpServer,
			"ftp_port":    ftpPort,
			"user_name":   userName,
			"password":    password,
			"passive":     passive,
			"ftp_transport_method":  ftp_transport_method,
			"file_destination_path": fileDestinationPath,
			"delete_after_upload":   "false",
			"file_format": file_format
		});
		
		//Encode the data into base64
		var StringUtil = GlideStringUtil;
		request.push(StringUtil.base64Encode(output));
		
		//Get the values we will need to pass to the MID Server Script Include to do the work
		request.push(fileDestinationPath);
		request.push(ftpServer);
		request.push(ftpPort);
		request.push(userName);
		request.push(password);
		request.push(ftp_transport_method);
		request.push(passive);
		request.push(midServerTempPath);
		request.push(false);
		request.push(file_format);
		
		return request;
	},	
	_sendFilePartToMIDServer: function(properties) {
		//Calls the MID Server Script Include
		var jp = new JavascriptProbe(properties.mid_server);
		jp.setName("FileBuilderFileCopy");
		jp.setJavascript("var req = new MidServerIntegration();req.processFilePart();");
		jp.addParameter("filePayload",       properties.payload);
		jp.addParameter("filename",          properties.file_name + ".part" + properties.part_number);
		jp.addParameter("targetpath", properties.temp_path);
		jp.addParameter("skip_sensor", true);
		jp.create();
	},
		
	_sendFinishFileToMIDServer: function(properties) {
		var jp = new JavascriptProbe(properties.mid_server);
		jp.setName("FileBuilderFileCopy");
		jp.setJavascript("var req = new MidServerIntegration();req.processFileFinish();");
		jp.addParameter("filePayload", properties.payload);
		jp.addParameter("finishFile",  properties.file_name + ".finish");
		jp.addParameter("filename",    properties.file_name);
		jp.addParameter("fileCount",   properties.file_count);
		jp.addParameter("targetpath", properties.temp_path);
		jp.addParameter("filepath", properties.file_destination_path);
		jp.addParameter("host", properties.ftp_server);
		jp.addParameter("port", properties.ftp_port);
		jp.addParameter("user", properties.user_name);
		jp.addParameter("password", properties.password);
		jp.addParameter("transportMethod",   properties.ftp_transport_method);
		jp.addParameter("passive",           properties.passive);
		//jp.addParameter("deleteAfterUpload", properties.delete_after_upload);
		jp.addParameter("deleteAfterUpload", "false");
		jp.addParameter("skip_sensor", true);
		jp.create();
	},
	type: 'MidServerIntegrationCalls'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2018-08-14 09:43:11</sys_created_on><sys_id>8dcba4274f331300370089dba310c7f4</sys_id><sys_mod_count>20</sys_mod_count><sys_name>MidServerIntegrationCalls</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Global" source="global">global</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_include_8dcba4274f331300370089dba310c7f4</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2018-08-22 09:14:53</sys_updated_on></sys_script_include></record_update>

        } else if (this.transportMethod == "FTPS (Implicit TLS)") {

        }</description><name>MidServerIntegration</name><script><![CDATA[/**
 * Author: hamza.berouil@gmail.com
 * Description: FTP Client for the MID server.
 * Provides interaction with an FTP server via the MID server
 */
var MidServerIntegration = Class.create();
MidServerIntegration.prototype = {
    initialize: function() {

        //Initialze all the libraries needed
        this.Properties = Packages.java.util.Properties;
        this.StringUtil = Packages.com.glide.util.StringUtil;
        this.BufferedWriter = Packages.java.io.BufferedWriter;
        this.File = Packages.java.io.File;
        this.FileWriter = Packages.java.io.FileWriter;
        this.Encrypter = new Packages.com.glide.util.Encrypter();
        this.FileOutputStream = Packages.java.io.FileOutputStream;
        this.FileReader = Packages.java.io.FileReader;
        this.FtpFile = Packages.org.ftp4che.util.ftpfile;
        this.FileInputStream = Packages.java.io.FileInputStream;
        this.BufferedReader = Packages.java.io.BufferedReader;
        this.InputStreamReader = Packages.java.io.InputStreamReader;
        this.OutputStraem = Packages.java.io.OutputStream;
        this.BufferedOutputStream = Packages.java.io.BufferedOutputStream;
        this.Thread = Packages.java.lang.Thread;
        this.StringBuilder = Packages.java.lang.StringBuilder;

        //Get Probe parameters
        this.host = probe.getParameter('host');
        this.port = probe.getParameter('port');
        if (this.port == '' || this.port == undefined || this.port == null) {
            this.port = 21;
        }
        this.user = probe.getParameter('user');
        this.password = this.Encrypter.decrypt(probe.getParameter("password"));
        this.filepath = probe.getParameter('filepath');
        this.match = probe.getParameter('match');
        this.filename = probe.getParameter('filename');
        this.targetpath = probe.getParameter('targetpath');
        this.deleteAfterUpload = "false";
        this.passive = probe.getParameter("passive");
        this.transportMethod = probe.getParameter("transportMethod");
        this.encpayload = probe.getParameter("filePayload");
        this.payload = this.StringUtil.base64Decode(this.encpayload);
        this.payloadBytes = this.StringUtil.base64DecodeAsBytes(this.encpayload);
        this.deleteAfterUpload = probe.getParameter("deleteAfterUpload");
        this.fileFormat = probe.getParameter("fileFormat");
    },

    /**
     * Description: Creates a record in the table ecc_queue
     *              Used to load files content into ServiceNow in 2 steps, first it
     *              copies the files in temporary folder of the Mid Server then then       *              MId Server sends the content via Web Services to ServiceNow
     *              Only on 1 connection to retrieve all files from one folder
     * Parameters:
     *              none
     * Returns:
     *              none
     */
    copyFiles: function() {
        try {
            var connection = this._connectionSetup();
            connection.connect(); //connect
            connection.noOperation(); //keep connection alive

            /* get files in array */
            var myFiles = connection.getDirectoryListing(this.filepath);
            var fileArray = myFiles.toArray();

            for (var i = 0; i < fileArray.length; i++) {
                this._downloadFile(fileArray[i], connection, this.targetpath);
            }

            connection.disconnect();
        } catch (e) {
            probe.createElement('Exception', e);
        }
    },

    /**
     * Description:
     *             Used to download a single file from an FTP Server
     * Parameters:
     *             filename : the name of the file we want to download
     *             connection : connection object to the FTP Server
     *             targethpath : the folder where the file is loaded
     * Returns:
     *             none
     */
    _downloadFile: function(fileName, connection, targetpath) {
        try {
            var fromFile = new Packages.org.ftp4che.util.ftpfile.FTPFile(this.filepath, fileName);
            var tempFile = new Packages.org.ftp4che.util.ftpfile.FTPFile(this.targetpath, fileName);

            if (fileName != "/." && fileName != "/..") {
                connection.downloadFile(fromFile, tempFile);
                connection.deleteFile(fromFile);

                var file = new this.File(targetpath + "\\" + fileName);
                var fileReader = new this.FileReader(file);
                var bufReader = new this.BufferedReader(fileReader);
                var sb = new this.StringBuilder();
                var line = bufReader.readLine();

                while (line != null) {
                    sb.append(line).append("\n");
                    line = bufReader.readLine();
                }
                var content = sb.toString();
                bufReader.close();
                probe.createElement('file', fileName + "\n" + content);
            }

        } catch (e) {
            probe.createElement('Exception', e);
        }
    },

    processFilePart: function() {
        this.log("Running FileBuilderFileCopy.processFilePart()");
        this.log(this.filename);
        this._writeFile(this.filename, this.targetpath, this.payloadBytes);
    },

    _writeFile: function(fileName, targetPath, fileContent) {
        this.log("Writing file " + fileName);
        var file = new this.File(targetPath + "/" + fileName);
        var fos = new this.FileOutputStream(file);
        fos["write(byte[])"](fileContent);
        fos.flush();
        fos.close();
    },

    processFileFinish: function() {
        var fileName = this.filename;
        var fileCount = probe.getParameter("fileCount");

        this.log("Running FileBuilderFileCopy.processFileFinish()");

        var retryInterval = 10; // seconds
        var retryCount = 6;

        var i;

        for (i = 0; i < retryCount; i++) {
            this.log("Validating file parts for " + fileName + "...");
            if (!this._validateFiles(fileName, fileCount)) {
                this.log("Files not all present...");
                this.Thread.sleep(retryInterval * 1000);
            } else {
                this.log("All file parts exist");
                this._processOldFile();
                this._combineFiles(fileName, fileCount);
                this._cleanupFiles(fileName, fileCount);
                this._processFileTransfer();
                break;
            }
        }
    },

    _validateFiles: function(fileName, fileCount) {
        this.log("validateFiles() -> Checking for " + fileCount + " parts of " + fileName);
        var i;
        for (i = 0; i < fileCount; i++) {
            if (!this._fileExists(this.targetpath + "/" + fileName + ".part" + (i + 1)))
                return false;
        }

        // If we got this far, all of the files existed, return true
        return true;
    },


    _fileExists: function(file) {
        var f = new this.File(file);
        var exists = f.isFile();

        this.log("fileExists() -> file -> " + file + ", exists -> " + exists);
        return exists;
    },

    _processOldFile: function() {
        var deleteFile = true;
        var fullFilePath = this.filepath + "/" + this.filename;
        var f = new this.File(fullFilePath);

        this.log("processOldFile(): fullFilePath -> " + fullFilePath);

        if (deleteFile && f.isFile()) {
            this.log("processOldFile(): deleting file");
            f["delete"]();
        } else if (f.isFile()) {
            this.log("processOldFile(): renaming file");
            var newFilePath = this.filepath + "/" + this.filename + ".archive_" + new Date().getTime();

            this.log("processOldFile(): newFilePath -> " + newFilePath);

            var f2 = new this.File(newFilePath);

            var renameSucceeded = f.renameTo(f2);

            this.log("processOldFile(): renameSucceeded -> " + renameSucceeded);
        }
    },

    _combineFiles: function(fileName, fileCount) {
        this.log("combineFiles() -> combining " + fileCount + " files for " + fileName);
        var outFile = new this.File(this.targetpath + "/" + fileName);
        var fw = new this.FileWriter(outFile, true);
        var out = new this.BufferedWriter(fw);

        var i, line;
        var inFile, fis, isr, br;
        for (i = 0; i < fileCount; i++) {
            inFile = new this.File(this.targetpath + "/" + fileName + ".part" + (i + 1));
            fis = new this.FileInputStream(inFile);
            isr = new this.InputStreamReader(fis);
            br = new this.BufferedReader(isr);

            line = null;
            while ((line = br.readLine()) != null) {
                out.write(line);
                out.newLine();
            }

            br.close();
        }

        out.close();
    },

    _cleanupFiles: function(fileName, fileCount) {
        this.log("cleanupFiles() -> " + fileName);
        var fullFilePath;
        var file;
        for (i = 0; i < fileCount; i++) {
            fullFilePath = this.targetpath + "/" + fileName + ".part" + (i + 1);
            this.log("cleanupFiles() -> removing " + fullFilePath);
            file = new this.File(fullFilePath);
            file["delete"]();
        }
    },

    _processFileTransfer: function() {
        if (this.transportMethod == "SFTP") {
            try {
                var localFileName = this.targetpath + "/" + this.filename;
                this.log("Copying from local file: " + localFileName);
                this._sftpFile(this.host, this.user, this.password, localFileName, this.filepath + this.filename);
            } catch (e) {
                this.log("Error in writing file to SFTP server: " + e);
            }
        } else {
            try {
                this._copyToFTP();
            } catch (e) {
                this.log("Error in writing the file: " + e);
            }
        }
    },
	
/** 
* Description: use the function uploadFile from the package FTPFile
* Parameters:  none
* Returns: none
*/ 
    _copyToFTP: function() {
        this.log("Copying to FTP");
        var tmpLoc;
        var connectionType;
        var connection = this._connectionSetup();

        this.log("copyToFTP(): filepath -> " + this.filepath);
        this.log("copyToFTP(): filename -> " + this.filename);

        var fromFile = new Packages.org.ftp4che.util.ftpfile.FTPFile(this.targetpath, this.filename);
        var toFile = new Packages.org.ftp4che.util.ftpfile.FTPFile(this.filepath, this.filename);

        var connectionLog = "Connection Log:\n";
        var connected = false;

        try {
            connection.connect();
            this.log("Connecting to " + this.host + " on port " + this.port);

            connection.noOperation();
            connected = true;
        } catch (e) {
            connectionLog += "\nException in block B: " + e;
            connected = false;
        }

        if (connected == true) {
            try {
                this.log("Connected...");
                this.log("Uploading " + fromFile + " to " + toFile);
                connection.uploadFile(fromFile, toFile);
                this.log("File successfully uploaded\n\n");
                connection.disconnect();
                if (this.deleteAfterUpload == "true") {
                    this.log("deleteAfterUpload -> " + this.deleteAfterUpload + ", deleting local file...");
                    new this.File(this.filepath + "/" + this.filename)["delete"]();
                }
            } catch (e) {
                connectionLog += "\n**********FAILURE: Connection to FTP server failed**************\n";
                connectionLog += "\nException in block C: \n" + e;
            }
        } else {
            connectionLog += "\n**********FAILURE: Connection to FTP server failed**************\n";
        }

        this.log(connectionLog);
    },

    /*
     * sftpFile - SFTP the file to an SFTP server
     *
     * @param hostName - server to connect to
     * @param userName - user name to log in as
     * @param password - password to go with the user name
     * @param localFileName - file to send ex. C:\ServiceNow\MIDServer1\agent\filebuilder\testfile.txt
     * @param remoteFileName - destination file ex. /home/user/testfile.txt
     *
     * @return none
     *
     */
    _sftpFile: function(hostName, userName, password, localFileName, remoteFileName) {

        this.log('sftpFile(): attempting to connect to ' + hostName);
        var ssh = new Packages.com.sshtools.j2ssh.SshClient();
        var ignoreHost = new Packages.com.sshtools.j2ssh.transport.IgnoreHostKeyVerification();
        if (!this.port) {
            this.port = 22;
        }
        this.log('sftpFile(): attempting to connect to ' + hostName + " on port " + this.port);
        ssh.connect(hostName, this.port, ignoreHost);

        pwd = new Packages.com.sshtools.j2ssh.authentication.PasswordAuthenticationClient();
        var authPassword = new Packages.com.glide.util.Encrypter().decrypt(password);
        pwd.setUsername(userName);
        pwd.setPassword(authPassword);

        // Get full path of filename
        //var sftpLocalFileName = new this.File(localFileName).getAbsolutePath();
        this.log('sftpFile(): attempting to copy ' + localFileName + ' to ' + remoteFileName);
        if (ssh.authenticate(pwd) == new Packages.com.sshtools.j2ssh.authentication.AuthenticationProtocolState().COMPLETE) {
            sftp = ssh.openSftpClient();

            try {
                sftp.put(localFileName, remoteFileName);
                this.log("File successfully uploaded\n\n");

                if (this.deleteAfterUpload == "true") {
                    this.log("deleteAfterUpload -> " + this.deleteAfterUpload + ", deleting local file...");
                    new this.File(localFileName)["delete"]();
                }
            } catch (e) {
                this.log('FILE NOT FOUND ' + remoteFileName + ' or error: ' + e);
            }
            sftp.quit();
            try {
                // kill connection
                ssh.disconnect();
            } catch (e) {
                this.log('Manual connection kill not successful with error: ' + e);
            }
        }

    },

    log: function(data) {
        ms.log(data);
    },


    /* Support function for setting up the connection*/
    _connectionSetup: function() {
        var pt = new Packages.java.util.Properties();
        pt.setProperty("connection.host", this.host);
        pt.setProperty("connection.port", this.port);
        pt.setProperty("user.login", this.user);
        pt.setProperty("user.password", this.password);
        pt.setProperty("connection.type", "FTP_CONNECTION");
        pt.setProperty("connection.timeout", "10000");
        pt.setProperty("connection.passive", "true");
        var connection = Packages.org.ftp4che.FTPConnectionFactory.getInstance(pt);
        return connection;
    },

    type: 'MidServerIntegration'
};]]></script><sys_class_name>ecc_agent_script_include</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2018-08-14 08:30:15</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_domain_path>/</sys_domain_path><sys_id>c29b682b4f331300370089dba310c7ce</sys_id><sys_mod_count>29</sys_mod_count><sys_name>MidServerIntegration</sys_name><sys_overrides/><sys_package display_value="Global" source="global">global</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>ecc_agent_script_include_c29b682b4f331300370089dba310c7ce</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2018-08-22 09:14:00</sys_updated_on></ecc_agent_script_include></record_update>

		var fileObj = obj['file'];
		for(var x in fileObj){
			if(typeof fileObj[x]!="function"){
				
				//Create a new transaction
				var newTransaction = new GlideRecord("u_ftp_transaction");
				var fileString = fileObj[x].toString();

				var content = fileString.replace(firstLine+'\n', '');

				newTransaction.u_type = firstLine.substring(14,17);
				newTransaction.insert();

		}
		
		current.state = 'processed';
		current.processed = gs.nowDateTime();
